{
  "doc_id": "410",
  "text": "Occurrence of the sarcomatous component in a mediastinal teratoma has no specific initial clinical feature. Teratomas that are likely to progress to such an outcome can not be differentiated from others on the basis of clinical or radiological criteria [CITATION_1] . Diagnosis can be fortuitous at the time of histopathological examination of a tumour biopsy or after tumour resection or, more frequently, as a result of an unusual outcome with chemotherapy of a presumed non-teratomatous germ-cell tumour [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
